{"timestamp": "2025-12-02 20:12:31.315622", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission complete.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"server_access_router\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"icmp_acl_block\"]\n\nRationale (concise):\n- Backend web subnet 20.200.0.0/24 is unreachable from most hosts but reachable from load balancer and backend peers — pattern consistent with intentional ACL-based segmentation applied at the server-access-router blocking ICMP (and likely other host-originated access) to the backend subnet.\n- Other explanations (routing omission, host firewalls) are less consistent with the observed selective reachability.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2584, "output_tokens": 123, "total_tokens": 2707, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
